{"_id":"e9bd4d27-c6ca-3b1d-bd5c-03f537cda357","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"No, it does not need CPU time or a thread.\r\n\r\nHard drives (and other I/O devices such as network cards, video cards, and even serial/parallel ports) have tiny dedicated processors that do the actual copying. The CPU only places the data in a DMA region and triggers a signal to the device. The device then copies it out of memory.","postId":"2013_11_there-is-no-thread-a4d25d49-dbfd-39fd-9b16-ff58dd4a1ff2","replyTo":"61f71b33-e69d-3944-8750-11c57ceb9b69","date":"2016-05-24T01:37:57Z","timestamp":1464053877,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"}